{
  "texts": [
    "Maximum and minimum number of items reported in the original abstract was 17 and 4, respectively, meanwhile GPT 3.5 displayed a narrower range between 12 and 3.",
    "GPT 4 demonstrated a maximum score of 11 and recorded a minimum score of 0 as GPT 4 produced 4 abstracts of an unrelated study, thereby falsely reporting all items of the CONSORT-A checklist.",
    "Table 3 demonstrates adherence of abstracts to each item of the CONSORT-A checklist.",
    "Comparable percentages of abstracts were identified as randomised in the title across all three groups (67.74% vs 67.74% vs 59.68%; original vs GPT 3.5 vs GPT 4, respectively).",
    "Trial designs did not differ between original and GPT 3.5, however the criterion was reported in a significantly higher percentage of original abstracts than the GPT 4 counterparts (41.94% vs 20.97%, respectively; P = 0.02) (see S1 Table for statistical comparison between all three groups)."
